  "body": "### Description\n\nCurrently the kubernetes-client supports a single client that targets a single cluster. \r\nIt would be great if it was possible to configure support for multiple clouds. \n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nWe could have something like a `Map<String, KubernetesConfig>` and have a named configuration per cluster. \r\nFor each key/name in that map we could produce a `KubernetesClient` bean, qualified by that name.",
